SUMMARY:Deadline: Arte Laguna Prize 2026 (21st Edition)
DESCRIPTION:International Arte Laguna Prize\, open to artists across many m
 edia including dedicated digital art and video sections\, with a finalist 
 exhibition at the Venice Arsenale Nord. ELIGIBILITY: individual artists of
  all ages and nationalities worldwide. NOTE: an entry fee applies (roughly
  EUR 97 to EUR 122)\, but the prize awards substantial cash. Apply via the
  Arte Laguna Prize page.\n\nOrganisation: Arte Laguna (Venice)\nLocation: 
 Venice\, Italy (finalist exhibition at Arsenale Nord)\nAward: EUR 10\,000 
 main prize plus additional FOMAS prizes (EUR 7\,000 / 4\,000 / 3\,000) and
  a finalist exhibition at the Venice Arsenale Nord. Entry fee approximatel
 y EUR 97 to EUR 122.\nDuration: One-off prize\n\nMore: https://artelagunap
 rize.com/21-edition/
URL:https://artelagunaprize.com/21-edition/
LOCATION:Venice\, Italy (finalist exhibition at Arsenale Nord)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:file-not-found-open-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260701T070201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Deadline: FILE NOT FOUND: Open Call for Archive Residencies
DESCRIPTION:Open call to participate in FILE NOT FOUND\, a project explorin
 g the risks and challenges archives face as sites of cultural memory\, res
 istant knowledge and alternative perspectives under growing political pres
 sure. Ten practitioners - artists\, thinkers\, activists\, theatre makers\
 , dancers\, musicians and more - will be selected for residencies at ten c
 ultural archives around the world. On site\, residents engage with existin
 g archival practices\, explore both safe and not-so-safe spaces\, investig
 ate traditional and experimental methods of archiving\, and ideally develo
 p artistically subversive approaches that strengthen the resilience of arc
 hives against external influence. ELIGIBILITY: artists worldwide\, all dis
 ciplines. Applicants review the ten participating archives and select the 
 one they wish to apply to. The on-site residency runs 2 weeks to 2 months 
 between August 2026 and May 2027. OUTCOME: an artwork plus a residency rep
 ort\, with a group exhibition at BLMK Cottbus\, Germany in autumn 2027. Wo
 rking language English.\n\nOrganisation: Goethe-Institut\nLocation: On-sit
 e at ten cultural archives around the world\; final exhibition at BLMK Cot
 tbus\, Germany\nAward: EUR 4\,000 (EUR 2\,000 artist fee + EUR 2\,000 prod
 uction budget). Travel and accommodation covered up to EUR 2\,000 for one 
 person.\nDuration: On-site residency of 2 weeks to 2 months\, scheduled be
 tween August 2026 and May 2027\n\nMore: https://www.goethe.de/prj/fnf/en/o
 ca.html
URL:https://www.goethe.de/prj/fnf/en/oca.html
LOCATION:On-site at ten cultural archives around the world\; final exhibiti
 on at BLMK Cottbus\, Germany
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:future-generation-art-prize-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260701T070201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260514
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260515
SUMMARY:Deadline: PinchukArtCentre: Future Generation Art Prize 2026
DESCRIPTION:Biennial international prize for individual artists or collecti
 ves worldwide aged 18-35. No application fee. Open to all visual-arts medi
 a\, including video\, installation\, performance\, photography. Excluded: 
 applicants with Russian or Belarusian citizenship/residency\, and former w
 inners. Shortlist announced late November 2026\; shortlisted artists are e
 xhibited at PinchukArtCentre in Kyiv and at a collateral event at the Veni
 ce Biennale 2027 (exhibition opens August 2027). Of the $40\,000 productio
 n investment for the main winner\, the funds are tied to producing new wor
 k. Strong fit for an artist working at the intersection of installation\, 
 video and critical AI/surveillance themes (an AI/drones installation would
  qualify as a video/installation submission). Tight age window (must be 35
  or under at deadline)\; the prize is positioned as career-launching for y
 ounger practitioners.\n\nOrganisation: PinchukArtCentre / Victor Pinchuk F
 oundation\nLocation: Worldwide (online application\; exhibition in Kyiv an
 d at Venice Biennale 2027)\nAward: Main Prize: $100\,000 ($60\,000 cash + 
 $40\,000 invested in production). Up to five Special Prizes of $20\,000 ea
 ch.\nDuration: Per artist\; exhibition cycle runs August 2027\n\nMore: htt
 ps://futuregenerationartprize.org/en/home-page-fgap
URL:https://futuregenerationartprize.org/en/home-page-fgap
LOCATION:Worldwide (online application\; exhibition in Kyiv and at Venice B
 iennale 2027)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:via-art-fund-artistic-production-fall-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260701T070201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260521
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260522
SUMMARY:Deadline: VIA Art Fund: Artistic Production Grant (Fall 2026 cycle)
DESCRIPTION:Production grants for newly commissioned works of visual art ex
 hibited beyond museum walls\, in the public realm\, or in non-traditional 
 exhibition environments. Grants are awarded to projects that best exemplif
 y VIA's three core values of Artistic Production\, Thought Leadership\, an
 d Public Engagement. Two-stage application process: Letter of Inquiry due 
 21 May 2026\; invitations to submit a full application sent 24 June 2026 (
 by invitation only)\; full application deadline for invited applicants 23 
 July 2026\; grant award notification November 2026. Projects must start af
 ter 15 December 2026. VIA runs Fall and Spring cycles each year\; Fall 202
 6 is the current open call.\n\nOrganisation: VIA Art Fund\nLocation: World
 wide (projects exhibited beyond museum walls\, in the public realm\, or in
  non-traditional exhibition environments)\nAward: $25\,000 to $100\,000 pe
 r project\nDuration: Per project (must start after 15 December 2026)\n\nMo
 re: https://viaartfund.org/apply/
URL:https://viaartfund.org/apply/
LOCATION:Worldwide (projects exhibited beyond museum walls\, in the public 
 realm\, or in non-traditional exhibition environments)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:boiler-room-broadcast-lab-14-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260701T070201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260517
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260518
SUMMARY:Deadline: Boiler Room Broadcast Lab #14 (2026)
DESCRIPTION:Open call for individual musicians\, collectives\, and curators
  to pitch a project to be streamed on Boiler Room. The fund looks to platf
 orm overlooked scenes and spaces\, innovative programming concepts that pr
 ioritise underrepresented artists\, marginalised communities\, and forward
 -thinking collaborations. While Boiler Room's archive is heavily DJ-focuse
 d\, applicants are encouraged to explore live performance\, instrumentatio
 n\, and non-club genres. Winning application receives up to GBP 10\,000 to
  bring the project to life\, plus additional in-kind support and a full re
 lease on Boiler Room's channels. Deadline: Sunday 17 May at 23:59 BST. Thi
 s is the 14th edition of Broadcast Lab.\n\nOrganisation: Boiler Room\nLoca
 tion: Worldwide (project streamed on Boiler Room channels)\nAward: Up to G
 BP 10\,000 to produce the project\, plus in-kind support from Boiler Room 
 and a full release across Boiler Room's channels\nDuration: Production tim
 eline TBD by project\; output is a streamed broadcast on Boiler Room.\n\nM
 ore: https://boilerroom.tv/broadcast-lab/
URL:https://boilerroom.tv/broadcast-lab/
LOCATION:Worldwide (project streamed on Boiler Room channels)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
